# Build folders
Debug/
Release/

# IDE local settings
.settings/

# Temporary files
*.o
*.d
*.su

# What is "Important"?
# In an STM32 project, "important" means the files required to rebuild the project from scratch.
# CategoryFiles     |       Folders to Keep         |         Why?
# Source Code       |       Src/, Inc/, drivers/    |    This is your actual logic and peripheral drivers.
# Configuration     |       .project/, .cproject/   |    These tell the IDE how to build your project.
# Hardware          |       Startup/, *.ld          |    Linker scripts and assembly startup files for the MCU.
# IOC File          |       *.ioc (if present)      |    The STM32CubeMX configuration file.


# What to Ignore?
# Debug/ or Release/: These contain .elf, .bin, and .o files generated during compilation.
# .settings/: Contains your personal IDE preferences (like theme or local toolchain paths).
